we argued that chaotic systems with absorption should be considered as a class of dynamical systems on its own . absorption converts the closed dynamics of trajectories into an open dynamics of weighted rays which we have shown to have fundamentally different chaos characteristics when compared to those of traditional open systems ( in which trajectories escape ) . among such properties are the new perron - frobenius operator ( [ eq.fp2 ] ) , an implicit formula ( [ eq.escaperate ] ) for the escape rate , a generalized kantz - grassberger relationship ( [ eq : ld_d1 ]
) for d maps , and an enhanced multifractality of invariant measures . we anticipate that absorption has also important consequences in other operator approaches based on markov partitions , which received renewed interest with the concept of almost invariant sets @xcite and ulam s method @xcite . furthermore , we conjecture that , provided the direct product structure seen in the baker example holds , for invertible chaotic 2d maps with absorption ( see tab . [ tab.cardioid ] for a numerical test ) . our results apply to any chaotic system with absorption or partial reflection , provide
new relations that have been looked after for decades @xcite , have direct implications for wave - chaotic systems @xcite , and are directly accessible to experiments ( e.g. , measuring the spatial distribution of decaying states in optical and acoustic systems ) . we are indebted to g. drtos , h. kantz , z. kaufmann , r. klages , p. grassberger , and t. weich for useful discussions . this work was supported by otka grant no . nk100296 , the von humboldt foundation , and the fraunhofer society . 99 h. kuttruff , . spon press , 2005
