delamination is a typical failure mode of composite materials caused by weak bonding . it arises when a crack initiates and propagates under a destructive loading . given the physical law characterizing the properties of the interlayer adhesive between the bonded bodies , we consider the problem of computing the propagation of the crack front and the stress field along the contact boundary . this leads to a hemivariational inequality , which after discretization by finite elements we solve by a nonconvex bundle method , where upper- criteria have to be minimized . as this is in contrast with other
classes of mechanical problems with non - monotone friction laws and in other applied fields , where criteria are typically lower- , we propose a bundle method suited for both types of nonsmoothness . we prove its global convergence in the sense of subsequences and test it on a typical delamination problem of material sciences . * key words . * composite material delamination crack front propagation hemivariational inequality clarke directional derivative nonconvex bundle method lower- and upper- function convergence . institut de mathmatiques , universit de toulouse , france ] institute of mathematics , department of aerospace engineering ,
