we observed sgr a * using the very large array ( vla ) and the giant metrewave radio telescope ( gmrt ) at multiple cm and mm wavelengths on 17 june 2003 . the measured flux densities of sgr a * , together with those obtained from the submillimeter array ( sma ) and the keck ii 10 m telescope on the same date , are used to construct a simultaneous spectrum of sgr a * from 90 cm to 3.8 m . the simultaneous spectrum shows a spectral break at about 3.6 cm , a possible signature of synchrotron
