the -cell embeddings of graphs on closed surfaces have been widely studied . it is well known that ( -cell ) embedding a given graph on a closed orientable surface is equivalent to cyclically ordering the edges incident to each vertex of . in this paper , we study the following problem : given a genus embedding of the graph and a vertex of , how many different ways of reembedding the vertex such that the resulting embedding is of genus ? we give formulas to compute this quantity and the local minimal genus achieved by reembedding . in the
