of decay of the turbulence increasing the decay from to . the hall effect has virtually no impact in this regard . the power spectra of density , velocity and the magnetic field are all affected by the non - ideal terms , being steepened significantly when compared with ideal mhd turbulence with exponents . the density power spectra components change from to for the ideal and non - ideal simulations respectively , and power spectra of the other variables all show similar modifications when non - ideal effects are considered . again , the dominant source of these changes
