thermoelectric coefficients of an ultra - thin topological insulator are presented here . the hybridization between top and bottom surface states of a topological insulator plays a significant role . in absence of magnetic field , thermopower increases and thermal conductivity decreases with increase of the hybridization energy . in presence of magnetic field perpendicular to the ultra - thin topological insulator , thermoelectric coefficients exhibit quantum oscillations with inverse magnetic field , whose frequency is strongly modified by the zeeman energy and phase factor is governed by the product of the lande -factor and the hybridization energy . in
