ar in the junction between the superconductor and the spin - resolved qh bulk state . a finite amount of equal - spin ar can be expected for a 2deg with strong spin - orbit interaction according to recent theoretical studies @xcite . therefore , we here assume coexistence of equal - spin ar and normal ar , corresponding to ar intermediated with and without a spin - flip process respectively , as schematically shown in fig . [ fig3](a ) . in order to more quantitatively interpret the sub - gap features including the side peaks , we construct
